    "Body": "Remote Woman Remote jobs at trusted companies Close Search for: Search Remote Jobs Marketing Design Developer Product Sales Support Success Stories Community Podcast Post Jobs Menu Business Content Writer Full Time Anywhere Posted 3 months ago This position has been filled Auth0 Overview Auth0 is a pre-IPO unicorn. We are growing rapidly and looking for exceptional new team members to add to our teams and will help take us to the next level. One team, one score. We never compromise on identity. You should never compromise yours either. We want you to bring your whole self to Auth0. If you\u2019re passionate, practice radical transparency to build trust and respect, and thrive when you\u2019re collaborating, experimenting and learning \u2013 this may be your ideal work environment. We are looking for team members that want to help us build upon what we have accomplished so far and make it better every day. N+1 > N. We are seeking a Business Content Writer to expand our ability to explain why technology strategy is business strategy and why IAM is central to business success. You will be responsible for brainstorming, creating, and transforming ideas into words for blog posts, landing pages, video scripts, whitepapers, and marketing campaigns. Our audience has zero tolerance for bs. The right candidate will avoid marketing-speak and hyperbole in favor of clarity and precision while still creating compelling and persuasive copy. This role can be based remotely from a home office. What You Will Do Help deepen our overall business content strategy and broader content marketing efforts by creating content to attract additional enterprise customers Develop different types of content (blog posts, whitepapers, landing pages, emails, videos, etc.) for diverse audiences Develop a compelling brand story, from strategic positioning or conceptual creative strategy, for all content pieces Revise, edit, and proofread content as needed or directed Help oversee and scrutinize the consistency and quality of our brand voice, ensuring that we always sound like us Assist in developing documentation to help streamline the work of others and increase consistency Help research key business decision-making personas What You Bring 5+ years of experience writing business content for a technical audience for a company and/or a news organization, or business analyst experience \u2014 B2B technology preferred Outstanding writing and verbal communication skills A link to your portfolio, blog, or site where we can view your work. Tech is not a means to a day gig \u2014 you either love tech, are fascinated by how it gets made, or both A deep understanding of how technology underpins business and economics. \u2018Fast and continual learner\u2019 is your default setting Strategic thinking, as well as strong execution skills If the information doesn\u2019t come to you, you go get it You bring flexibility \u2013 short, long, multiple story formats, new experiment? You\u2019re game. You are an agile team player with the ability to thrive in a fast-paced startup environment where direction and goals can evolve quickly Great interpersonal skills and the ability to engage with many internal/external groups You believe that deadlines will set us all free (and are happy to help others hit them) Experience and comfortable with a remote working environment Extra points for Adobe Premiere video editing, cybersecurity content experience and demonstrated IAM expertise Auth0\u2019s mission is to help developers innovate faster. Every company is becoming a software company and developers are at the center of this shift. They need better tools and building blocks so they can stay focused on innovating. One of these building blocks is identity: authentication and authorization. That\u2019s what we do. Our platform handles 2.5B logins per month for thousands of customers around the world. From indie makers to Fortune 500 companies, we can handle any use case. We like to think that we are helping make the internet safer. We have raised $210M to date and are growing quickly. Our team is spread across more than 35 countries and we are proud to continually be recognized as a great place to work. Culture is critical to us, and we are transparent about our vision and principles. Join us on this journey to make developers more productive while making the internet safer! More Jobs Website Twitter Or view all jobs: Developer jobs Marketing jobs Product jobs Design jobs Sales jobs Support jobs & learn about: remote work Related Jobs Fundraising Content Program Manager Wikimedia Wikimedia is a global movement whose mission is to bring free educational content to the world. Anywhere Full Time Posted 3 weeks ago Director, Field Marketing Americas GitHub The world's leading software development platform Anywhere Full Time Posted 3 months ago Senior Brand Manager Komoot Change The Way People Explore Anywhere Full Time Posted 1 month ago MAIN Podcast Community Post a job Remote Work Virtual Wedding Instagram Twitter Login REMOTE JOBS Developer jobs Marketing jobs Product jobs Design jobs Sales jobs Support jobs JOBS IN YOUR CITY Los Angeles jobs New York City jobs San Francisco jobs Chicago jobs Seattle jobs Austin jobs London jobs Paris jobs Berlin jobs POST YOUR JOBS Post a job We\u2019ve helped the world\u2019s top companies hire a talented, diverse pool of job candidates \u2013 view our success stories here. Terms & Privacy Policy & hello@remotewoman.com @ 2020 RemoteWoman \u2014 All Rights Reserved My account Post a job Back to Top Marketing Developer Design Product Sales Support"
